                            <comment id="12423423" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Tue, 25 Jul 2006 20:45:53 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.  Thanks Bertrand!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes, the encoding right now is controlled by the content-type header, not any possible XML charset declaration in the XML itself.  The servlet asks for a Reader, not for an InputStream, so we get chars that have already been decoded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe a future enhancement would use a Reader if content-type were specified, otherwise use an InputStream and let the XML parser try and figure out the encoding?&lt;/p&gt;
